---
title: "Dev Validation Test"
---

This is an internal page used to validate the development-only validation overlay and bootstrap-failure panel across frameworks. It is intentionally left out of the site navigation.

## Overlay over a live grid

A diagnostic captured while the grid is running is shown in an overlay over the grid. Here `sideBar: true` is set without the enterprise SideBar module, so a missing-module error is surfaced.

{% gridExampleRunner title="Overlay" name="overlay" /%}

## Legacy theme

The same overlay under a legacy theme rather than the Theming API, to check the legacy-theme styling.

{% gridExampleRunner title="Legacy Theme" name="legacy-theme" /%}

## Bootstrap failure panel

When grid creation aborts before the grid exists (here a `serverSide` row model with no row-model module registered), there is no grid to overlay, so a standalone panel is rendered in its place.

{% gridExampleRunner title="Bootstrap" name="bootstrap" /%}

## Nested (master/detail) grids

Each grid surfaces its own diagnostics on its own overlay, so a diagnostic emitted by a detail grid stays on that detail grid and the master grid is unaffected. Here the detail grid sets an invalid option; the first row auto-expands so the error surfaces on load.

{% gridExampleRunner title="Master Detail" name="master-detail" /%}

## Per-grid attribution across grids

Two independent grids share the page, each valid on load. Each grid has its own buttons that trigger a diagnostic on that grid:

- "Trigger warning" updates an initial-only option after creation (warning #22).
- "Trigger error" applies a theme with an invalid param value (error #107), emitted while the grid regenerates its styles.
- "Trigger async warning" runs an async transaction whose non-string row id is reported once the grid flushes it on a later frame (warning #25).

The overlay always appears on the grid that emitted the diagnostic, leaving the other grid untouched. The async and theme cases are the ones that previously broadcast to every grid before diagnostics were attributed to their originating grid.

Grid A also has a "Destroy grid, then call API" button. Calling the API of a destroyed grid (warning #26) can't be attributed to any grid, so — unlike the cases above — it surfaces on the other, still-live grid.

{% gridExampleRunner title="Multi Grid Attribution" name="multi-grid-attribution" /%}

## Structured error parameters

Some diagnostics carry array or object parameters, which must survive being encoded into the error-page URL and decoded back. This grid emits two: an unregistered `aggFunc` surfaces error #109 (its suggestions are an array), and an unregistered `cellRenderer` surfaces error #101 (its component maps are objects). Open each error page from the overlay to check both round-trip correctly.

{% gridExampleRunner title="Structured Params" name="structured-params" /%}
